  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Experience and Interface Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Primary Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Design user-centered interface for the client.</li>\n  <li>Create intuitive navigation systems for live and historical content</li>\n  <li>Develop accessibility-compliant designs meeting client's digital service standards</li>\n  <li>Design mobile-responsive interfaces optimized for various devices and screen sizes</li>\n  <li>Create user journey maps and interaction flows for different user personas</li>\n  <li>Conduct usability testing and iterate designs based on stakeholder feedback</li>\n  <li>Ensure design consistency with client's digital identity and branding guidelines</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Required Experience and Qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 5 years experience in UX/UI design for government digital services</li>\n  <li>Proven track record designing accessible interfaces compliant with WCAG 2.1 AA standards</li>\n  <li>Experience with Singapore Government Design System and digital service standards</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of government user research methodologies and stakeholder engagement processes</li>\n  <li>Understanding of client's user needs and constraints</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in design tools including Figma, Adobe Creative Suite, and prototyping platforms</li>\n  <li>Experience designing for real-time applications and data-intensive interfaces</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of multilingual interface design and cultural considerations for diverse user groups</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with government approval processes for design and branding compliance</li>\n  <li>Experience conducting user testing within government security environments</li>\n</ul>",
